@startuml sq_historyrepository01_create_snapshot
' ============================================================
' Title:     HISTORYREPO-01 — createSnapshot
' Boundary:  NASIM Application — Repository Layer
' Purpose:   Create a point-in-time snapshot of the session for
'             revert operations.
' Intro:     Data-access layer for session snapshots. Called by
'             Session Service during snapshot operations.
' Summary:   Snapshots capture full session state including messages,
'             metadata, and turn boundaries.
' Milestone: v1.0
' Version:   10.0.0
' Source:    docs/C4/c4_nasim_component.puml (v13.0.0), docs/UC/uc_history_repo.puml
' Review:    SQ Architect extraction 2026-07-01
' CSR Chain: Session Service → History Repository
' SM States: sm_session_svc_session.puml — ACTIVE → SAVED (snapshot)
' ============================================================

!include ../common/sq_styles.puml

title nasim — HISTORYREPO-01 createSnapshot

box "Service" SERVICE_COLOR
  participant "Session Service" as sessionSvc
end box

box "Repository" REPOSITORY_COLOR
  participant "History Repository" as historyRepo
end box

== HISTORYREPO-01 createSnapshot — entry ==

sessionSvc -> historyRepo : HISTORYREPO-01 createSnapshot({sessionId, turnIndex})
activate historyRepo

historyRepo -> historyRepo : serializeSessionState({sessionId})
historyRepo -> historyRepo : writeSnapshot({snapshot})

historyRepo --> sessionSvc : 200 OK — {snapshotId, createdAt}
deactivate historyRepo

== Summary ==
' HISTORYREPO-01 creates immutable snapshots for session revert.
' Snapshots are stored separately from the live session to avoid
' interference with ongoing operations.

@enduml
